{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"76b3bf43-f4f2-4945-866e-23a4b3d0dfe7","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication options (`--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example with auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific auth option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9b1ee2fc-c8ce-4341-b533-b67ed8f9246d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":279,"requestId":"FC06:20D256:17D3C05:1AF1C13:69FE8501"},"id":"998ed92d-b1de-4a65-9e0f-254f31787227","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:20.456Z","parentId":"00ceaf8f-919d-45ba-acf4-4aad8ee95e8e"}
